Germany  offered 120 million euros
($160 million) in aid to fund clean-energy projects in southern
 Africa .  Economic Cooperation Minister Dirk Niebel pledged the money
at United Nations climate talks in Durban,  South Africa ,
Germanyâ€™s  Environment Ministry  said today in  a statement  on its
website.  The money will fund solar power plants in South Africa and
link renewable energy projects across the southern part of the
